                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13753064" author="jxiang" created="Thu, 29 Aug 2013 00:03:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s a good catch. Dynamic class loading should be done in RS side only. Do we have a way to detect it is client side or server side?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13753069" author="ndimiduk" created="Thu, 29 Aug 2013 00:05:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While this change is being made, TestProtobufUtil should be moved into hbase-client so that its location is consistent with ProtobufUtil.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13860400" author="jxiang" created="Thu, 2 Jan 2014 17:52:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Instead of throwing a RuntimeException, the patch logs a warning, so that things can still work if dynamic class loading is not needed at all.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13860476" author="ndimiduk" created="Thu, 2 Jan 2014 18:16:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch works around the problem, doesn&apos;t really solve it. What happens when this code runs on the RegionServer, the directory isn&apos;t created/doesn&apos;t exist, and only the warning is printed? Does the process limp along in a broken state?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nit: the test doesn&apos;t explicitly create this condition, it just assumes the user running the test won&apos;t have access to that path. It also assumes a UNIX directory structure, so will not work on Windows.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13860549" author="jxiang" created="Thu, 2 Jan 2014 18:33:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s right. It works around the problem.  The issue is that we don&apos;t know if it is in the server side or client side. Let me check if I can add some checking in the server side. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13860828" author="jxiang" created="Thu, 2 Jan 2014 21:52:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Other solutions I thought about are all hacks. Should we leave this as Won&apos;t Fix?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13861682" author="jxiang" created="Fri, 3 Jan 2014 17:22:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close it as Won&apos;t Fix for now since no activity. Please feel free to re-open it if a better solution is found.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
